org.matsim.contrib.networkEditor.visualizing

Class NetBlackboard

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container
        • javax.swing.JComponent
          • javax.swing.JPanel
            • org.matsim.contrib.networkEditor.visualizing.NetBlackboard
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ImageObserver, MenuContainer, Serializable, Accessible

    public class NetBlackboard
extends JPanel
    This class just underwent fairly extensive manual refactoring because I wanted to get rid in the setX/Y in the standard Coord implementation. The way forward consisted of the following elements:
    • A new class MutableCoord, which has the setters, and is in general used in the present class.
    • A new interface CoordI, which just has the getters.
    • Make the static core methods accept the interface. The core should remain on the Coord class, to be sure that the values are immutable.
        kai, jul'16
    Author:
    danielmaxx
